<subSubSection id="99F2651FFFBCFFE6FF1CF91B4C0BFCBE" pageId="13" pageNumber="106" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D1573694FFBCFFE6FF1CF91B4B14F8D5" blockId="13.[113,764,1740,1924]" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBCFFE6FF1CF91B498EF915" box="[151,236,1741,1764]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">Notes. –</emphasis>
In the protologue, 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFBCFFE6FE4CF91A4BCBF915" author="BURMAN" box="[455,681,1740,1764]" firstAuthor="BURMAN" journalOrPublisher="Amsterdam" page="237" pageId="13" pageNumber="106" refId="ref8940" refString="BURMAN, N. L. (1768). Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis. Amsterdam." title="Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis" type="book" year="1768">BURMAN (1768: 237)</bibRefCitation>
cited a 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBCFFE6FFFAF93B49D2F8F5" box="[113,176,1773,1796]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">Pryon</emphasis>
specimen, as well as an illustration (
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFBCFFE6FDC9F93A49EAF8D5" author="RUMPHIUS, G. E." pageId="13" pageNumber="106" refId="ref10148" refString="RUMPHIUS, G. E. [BURMAN, J. (ed.)] (1741 - 1750). Herbarium Amboinense. 6 vol. Amsterdam, The Hague, Utrecht. [vol. 6, 1750]" type="book" year="1750">RUMPHIUS, 1750: 77</bibRefCitation>
, tab. 34, fig. 2) under the (unnamed) variety 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBCFFE6FDEBF8DA4B0DF8D5" box="[608,623,1804,1828]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">β</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1573694FFBCFFE6FF1CF8FB4BDFF875" blockId="13.[113,764,1740,1924]" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFBCFFE6FF1CF8FB48E2F8B5" author="MERRILL" box="[151,384,1836,1860]" firstAuthor="MERRILL" journalOrPublisher="Philippine J. Sci." page="335" pageId="13" pageNumber="106" pagination="329 - 388" part="19" refId="ref9969" refString="MERRILL, E. D. (1921). A review of the new species of plants proposed by N. L. Burman in his Flora Indica. Philippine J. Sci. 19: 329 - 388." title="A review of the new species of plants proposed by N. L. Burman in his Flora Indica" type="journal article" year="1921">MERRILL (1921: 335)</bibRefCitation>
referred to the 
<typeStatus id="0E538836FFBCFFE6FDBCF8FB4B05F8B4" box="[567,615,1837,1861]" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">type</typeStatus>
as “an actual specimen from 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBCFFE6FE9CF89B4837F895" box="[279,341,1869,1892]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">Pryon</emphasis>
, probably of Javan origin”, but unfortunately, no 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBCFFE6FF56F8BB4879F875" box="[221,283,1901,1924]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">Pryon</emphasis>
specimen could be found in G-PREL.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1573694FFBCFFE6FCCCFEC14A1AFE3E" blockId="13.[801,1455,279,847]" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">
An uncited specimen [G00349568] from unknown origin is however extant in G-PREL and should be regarded as original material; it bears a reference to Rumphius’ illustration in J. Burman’s handwriting with a slip of the pen (tab. 39 instead of tab. 34, the former representing a species of 
<taxonomicName id="16E84D17FFBCFFE6FAA9FE414A0FFE3E" authority="P. Beauv." authorityName="P. Beauv." class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Selaginellales" pageId="13" pageNumber="106" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBCFFE6FAA9FE414CF0FE5E" box="[1314,1426,407,431]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">Selaginella</emphasis>
P. Beauv.
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1573694FFBCFFE6FCCCFE014D44FCFE" blockId="13.[801,1455,279,847]" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFBCFFE6FCCCFE014DAAFE1E" author="CHAMBERS &amp; FARRANT" box="[839,1224,471,495]" firstAuthor="CHAMBERS" journalOrPublisher="Telopea" page="535" pageId="13" pageNumber="106" pagination="509 - 557" part="4" refId="ref8967" refString="CHAMBERS, T. C. &amp; P. A. FARRANT (1991). Are-examination of the genus Cheilanthes (Adiantaceae) in Australia. Telopea 4: 509 - 557." title="Are-examination of the genus Cheilanthes (Adiantaceae) in Australia" type="journal article" year="1991">CHAMBERS &amp; FARRANT (1991: 535</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFBCFFE6FB58FE014C2BFE1E" author="CHAMBERS &amp; FARRANT" box="[1235,1353,471,495]" editor="ORCHARD, A. E. &amp; P. M. MCCARTHY MCCARTHY" firstAuthor="CHAMBERS" page="278" pageId="13" pageNumber="106" pagination="271 - 286" part="48" refId="ref9057" refString="CHAMBERS, T. C. &amp; P. A. FARRANT (1998 b). Adiantaceae, Cheilanthes. In: ORCHARD, A. E. &amp; P. M. MCCARTHY MCCARTHY (ed.), Fl. Australia 48: 271 - 286." title="Adiantaceae, Cheilanthes" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Fl. Australia" year="1998" yearSuffix="b">1998b: 278</bibRefCitation>
) cited as 
<typeStatus id="0E538836FFBCFFE6FCAAFE214A1CFDFE" box="[801,894,503,527]" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">holotype</typeStatus>
two collections at 
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFBCFFE6FBCFFE214D38FDFE" box="[1092,1114,503,527]" country="Switzerland" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15706" name="Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques de la Ville de Genève" pageId="13" pageNumber="106" type="Herbarium">G</collectionCode>
(“ 
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFBCFFE6FBFFFE214DE5FDFE" box="[1140,1159,503,527]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">T</collectionCode>
: 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBCFFE6FB1AFE214C5CFDFE" box="[1169,1342,503,527]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">
<location id="D437604FFFBCFFE6FB1AFE214C5CFDFE" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:59418782FFBCFFE6FFFAFA214C0BFCBE:D437604FFFBCFFE6FB1AFE214C5CFDFE" box="[1169,1342,503,527]" country="Sri Lanka" municipality="Burman" name="Planta Zeylanica" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">Planta Zeylanica</location>
</emphasis>
collection (
<collectingCountry id="A9FF7604FFBCFFE6FCA2FDC14AF5FDDE" box="[809,919,535,559]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
). 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBCFFE6FC22FDCE4D54FDDE" box="[937,1078,536,559]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFBCFFE6FC22FDCE4AA3FDDE" box="[937,961,536,559]" country="China" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13092" name="Nanjing University" pageId="13" pageNumber="106" type="Herbarium">N</collectionCode>
. 
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFBCFFE6FC4EFDCE4AB5FDDE" box="[965,983,536,559]" country="Netherlands" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15678" name="Nationaal Herbarium Nederland, Leiden University branch" pageId="13" pageNumber="106" type="Herbarium">L</collectionCode>
. 
<collectingMunicipality id="3133ACEEFFBCFFE6FC6AFDCE4D54FDDE" box="[993,1078,536,559]" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">Burman</collectingMunicipality>
</emphasis>
(holo: 
<specimenCode id="814E9EEFFFBCFFE6FB09FDC14DAFFDDE" box="[1154,1229,535,559]" collectionCode="G" country="Switzerland" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15706" name="Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques de la Ville de Genève" pageId="13" pageNumber="106" type="Herbarium">G 1416</specimenCode>
[= 
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFBCFFE6FB79FDC14C6AFDDE" box="[1266,1288,535,559]" country="Switzerland" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15706" name="Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques de la Ville de Genève" pageId="13" pageNumber="106" type="Herbarium">Gloan</collectionCode>
number!], 2 sheets”), originated from two different herbaria and both sheets were annotated by 
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFBCFFE6FBC0FD814D3DFD9E" box="[1099,1119,599,623]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">T</collectionCode>
. 
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFBCFFE6FBE8FD814D1AFD9E" box="[1123,1144,599,623]" country="Denmark" name="University of Copenhagen" pageId="13" pageNumber="106" type="Herbarium">C</collectionCode>
. 
<location id="D437604FFFBCFFE6FB0DFD814D9CFD9E" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:59418782FFBCFFE6FFFAFA214C0BFCBE:D437604FFFBCFFE6FB0DFD814D9CFD9E" box="[1158,1278,599,623]" country="Sri Lanka" name="Chambers" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">Chambers</location>
: 1) the uncited specimen mentioned above (G-PREL [
<specimenCode id="814E9EEFFFBCFFE6FB43FDA14C2DFD7E" box="[1224,1359,631,655]" collectionCode="G" country="Switzerland" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15706" name="Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques de la Ville de Genève" pageId="13" pageNumber="106" type="Herbarium">G00349568</specimenCode>
]); and 2) a 
<collectingCountry id="A9FF7604FFBCFFE6FCBEFD414AE7FD5E" box="[821,901,663,687]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">Ceylon</collectingCountry>
collection from Houttuyn’s herbarium (see above Introduction), probably collected by 
<collectorName id="7C1D5342FFBCFFE6FB32FD614C41FD3E" box="[1209,1315,695,719]" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">Thunberg</collectorName>
in the years 1777 – 1778 (G-PREL [
<specimenCode id="814E9EEFFFBCFFE6FB99FD014DFAFD1E" box="[1042,1176,727,751]" collectionCode="G" country="Switzerland" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15706" name="Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques de la Ville de Genève" pageId="13" pageNumber="106" type="Herbarium">G00349567</specimenCode>
]). Therefore, this typification cannot be accepted.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1573694FFBCFFE6FCCCFCC14C0BFCBE" blockId="13.[801,1455,279,847]" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">The lectotypification is based here on the single specimen of original material present in G-PREL [G00349568].</paragraph>
